  "name": "Crafting Mundane Items",
  "description": "A character who has proficiency with the appropriate artisan's tools can craft nonmagical items. The character must have access to raw materials worth half the item's selling cost. For every day of downtime spent crafting, the character can craft items worth a total of 5 GP. If something to be crafted has a cost greater than 5 GP, the character makes progress each day in 5 GP increments until the total cost is reached. Multiple characters can combine their efforts to craft a single item, provided they all have proficiency with the requisite tools. Each character contributes 5 GP worth of effort per day.",
